00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:55,033
Hold your water, Jake.
The females have eggs.

246
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:58,311
So we're gonna stop everything
and pass out cigars?

247
00:22:58,360 --> 00:23:02,319
We're being paid to see
where they go, how they propagate.

248
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:07,115
If we had decent funding, I'd study
their motor systems, temperature...

249
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:11,551
We'd do a decent report for a change
and really give them something.

250
00:23:11,600 --> 00:23:14,956
If you'd leave me alone,
I'd be able to do my work.

251
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:17,355
I know how to tag a damn conch.

252
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:20,278
- Your readings suck, man.
- The tags suck.

253
00:23:20,320 --> 00:23:23,437
- No, it's I that made them.
- It's I that put 'em on.

254
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:26,313
- You put 'em on wrong.
- No, no, no! They leak!

255
00:23:26,360 --> 00:23:28,555
A blind man could find more conch!

256
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:31,319
You can't find your ass
with both hands!

257
00:23:31,360 --> 00:23:37,390
That's not fair! You go away, come
back a zombie, it's Christmas Eve.

258
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:40,000
- We're working overtime cos of YOU!
- Hey!

259
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:47,749
I'm sorry about your brother, man.

260
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:52,758
Well, just...
just take it easy, will ya?

261
00:23:57,840 --> 00:23:59,512
Jake.

262
00:24:02,760 --> 00:24:05,399
C'mon, Jake, don't...
I don't want...

263
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:09,274
- Oh! Put me down.
- I missed you, man!

264
00:24:09,320 --> 00:24:13,279
And then he wrote dirty words
all over the garage.

265
00:24:13,320 --> 00:24:16,630
He was... your daddy was five.
He was your age.

266
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:18,716
- I'm almost six.
- So is Jake.

267
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:23,351
Oh, look at that face.
OK, do the other one.

268
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:28,469
Now that's closer to the real truth.

269
00:24:28,520 --> 00:24:32,479
Oh, you. This guy was always
getting into some sort of mischief.

270
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:34,476
I got no doubt about that.

271
00:24:34,520 --> 00:24:38,115
Was Uncle Sean ever bad?
Did you ever spank him?

272
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:45,832
Sharp shirt, Jake.

273
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:48,997
Hey, may your sex life
be as busy as your shirt.

274
00:24:49,040 --> 00:24:51,315
Why, thank you.

275
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:53,430
My tea set! I got my tea set!

276
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:55,277
Oh, let me see!

277
00:24:55,320 --> 00:24:58,596
Every lovely lady
should have a tea set.

278
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:01,473
It has a teapot
and cups and saucers.

279
00:25:01,520 --> 00:25:04,432
And a sugar bowl
and a creamer.

280
00:25:04,480 --> 00:25:08,632
Can I put real tea in it?
Yes, real tea.

281
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:11,797
Can I make sandwiches?
Yes.

282
00:25:11,840 --> 00:25:15,037
Thea, we forgot
the Christmas carols.

283
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:19,710
Carol from the grocery store?
Oh, will you stop it?

284
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:28,318
I miss him, Mom.

285
00:25:30,760 --> 00:25:34,958
- I want you to change your work.
- Mom, please don't start that.

286
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:38,595
- You could teach or write...
- I'm not gonna quit now.

287
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:47,949
You're all I have left. I don't want
you working in the water.

288
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:55,956
Mom, what I do is perfectly safe.

289
00:25:57,080 --> 00:26:00,277
At the moment,
we're collecting big snails.

290
00:26:03,240 --> 00:26:06,391
Jake and I are scientists.
We're almost PhDs.

291
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:09,876
We know what we're doing.
There's nothing to worry about.

292
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:28,153
Oh, great.

293
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:35,157
And, well, we have to dig
the ditch really deep...

294
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:39,193
so the water'll go all the way
around and we can swim in it.

295
00:26:39,240 --> 00:26:41,549
You're silly.

296
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:45,354
You know what? Let's pretend
this is Buckingham Palace.

297
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:49,552
And you'll be Princess Di,
and we'll have a parade with horses.

298
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:52,512
And you'll ride in a golden carriage,
and we'll...

299
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:55,950
And I can invite
Cinderella to the ball.

300
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:59,436
She'll come
in a golden carriage, too.

301
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:03,234
And we can have
cookies and punch and cake.

302
00:27:03,280 --> 00:27:06,477
And I can invite
Prince Charlie and...

303
00:27:06,520 --> 00:27:08,988
What's the name
of the other prince?

304
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:18,837
Grandma? Grandma?

305
00:27:18,880 --> 00:27:20,359
What's wrong?

306
00:27:20,400 --> 00:27:22,277
Nothing.

307
00:27:22,320 --> 00:27:26,632
Oh, we better get this done
before the tide comes in.

308
00:27:26,680 --> 00:27:28,830
It's not nice to be evasive.

309
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:32,270
My mother says that
to my father all the time.

310
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:35,238
Hello, you two!

311
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:36,793
Hello.

312
00:27:39,320 --> 00:27:41,231
I don't know why I fish here.

313
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:44,955
I never catch anything.

314
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:49,312
There must be a sign underwater -
"beware, Hoagie's about".

315
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:53,148
- You drive the plane.
- Flies the plane.

316
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:56,192
Mostly, it's like driving.

317
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:58,151
What's that, an excavation?

318
00:27:58,200 --> 00:28:01,351
We're building a sand castle,
and you're invited for tea.

319
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:03,550
You know why you got
no ambition?

320
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:08,953
- Why is that, Jake?
- Your Norman Rockwell life.

321
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:10,433
Norman Rockwell?

322
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:13,119
That's precisely
your problem, my friend.

323
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:15,628
You weren't exactly a deprived kid.

324
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:19,036
I don't buy that
roots-rock-reggae bullshit.

325
00:28:19,080 --> 00:28:22,072
Cut that hair,
you're a three-piece suit.

326
00:28:22,120 --> 00:28:26,079
The bottom line is we got three
months left of work and no money.

327
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:27,473
Spent it all on beer.

328
00:28:27,520 --> 00:28:31,957
Bahamian Fisheries Department
is not exactly Fort Knox, my friend.

329
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:33,797
But, on the other hand,

330
00:28:33,840 --> 00:28:37,389
Office of Naval Research,
they've got money.

331
00:28:37,440 --> 00:28:39,351
No. Forget it.

332
00:28:39,400 --> 00:28:41,516
What do you mean? Money is money.

333
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:46,236
- They put bombs on dolphins.
- What you talking about?

334
00:28:46,280 --> 00:28:49,113
I know a guy who got money
from them to study eels.

335
00:28:49,160 --> 00:28:51,754
It's hard to put a bomb
on an eel!

336
00:28:51,800 --> 00:28:54,109
Who rattled your cage? Michael, man!

337
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:57,516
We're bustin' our bunghies
to get our degrees.

338
00:28:57,560 --> 00:28:59,869
I'm tired of all this paradise shit.

339
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:02,115
It's getting on my last nerve, man.

340
00:29:02,160 --> 00:29:04,355
William. Look at you, boy.

341
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:06,960
- What?
- A mental midget reading all day.

342
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:10,515
If mediocrity were fattening,
you'd all be whales.

343
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:12,073
Knock off that drummin'!

344
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:15,635
Look at you, boy.
What's wrong with you?

345
00:29:15,680 --> 00:29:19,832
You think because you been to
university you're smart?

346
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:23,395
I don't know
why I've told you all this.

347
00:29:23,440 --> 00:29:26,716
Sometimes talking
to a stranger is easier.

348
00:29:26,760 --> 00:29:30,230
I can't explain it.
It's just something I feel.

349
00:29:30,280 --> 00:29:33,272
I always listen to my feelings.

350
00:29:37,040 --> 00:29:41,431
I think I'm going crazy.
Nightmares and...

351
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:43,471
Maybe it was an accident.

352
00:29:43,520 --> 00:29:45,272
It was no accident.

353
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:47,151
I'm not saying you're wrong.

354
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:50,829
I'm just saying that maybe
there are other possibilities.

355
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:54,589
When it killed Sean, I knew
with certainty it had come for him.

356
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:56,437
I knew that!

357
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:57,993
I know it's coming.

358
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:02,069
I know it's coming.

359
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:06,269
What's it cost to ride on that plane?

360
00:30:06,320 --> 00:30:09,437
The water's coming in!
The water's coming in!

361
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:12,313
Depends on where you want to go.

362
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:14,794
- Doesn't matter.
- Hurry!

363
00:30:14,840 --> 00:30:18,037
- Just like that?
- Just like that.

364
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:21,914
Oh! Oh, no! Oh! Oh!

365
00:30:23,120 --> 00:30:26,078
Take the wheel!
I'm sorry?

366
00:30:26,120 --> 00:30:29,157
- Take the wheel.
- No, I can't.

367
00:30:29,200 --> 00:30:31,509
- Sure, you can.
- I don't know how.

368
00:30:31,560 --> 00:30:34,199
Nobody does till they learn.

369
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:38,153
What are you doing?

370
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:41,237
Better take the wheel
or we'll be swimming soon.

371
00:30:41,280 --> 00:30:44,033
Whoa, take it easy!
Take it easy!

372
00:30:44,080 --> 00:30:47,197
Hold her gently.
She'll damn near fly herself.

373
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:55,511
See? Just like driving a car.

374
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:57,471
Where do I pull off the road?

375
00:30:57,520 --> 00:31:01,433
No, you're doing fine.
I'll keep you out of trouble.

376
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:04,313
- Relax.
- Where are we going?

377
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:07,272
One time, I was flying supplies
up the Amazon

378
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:09,311
when I came down in the jungle.

379
00:31:09,360 --> 00:31:12,193
- You won't tell me?
- I was picked up by head-hunters,

380
00:31:12,240 --> 00:31:13,753
and taken to their chief.

381
00:31:13,800 --> 00:31:16,155
- You are impossible!
- He looked at me

382
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:18,111
and took me in his hut.

383
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:21,118
Inside his hut,
there was a long pole...

384
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:36,672
What is all this?

385
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:40,190
Just a little something
I arranged to cheer you up.

386
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:41,719
- No, really.
- What?

387
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:44,832
- Tell me, what is all this?
- A local festival.

388
00:31:44,880 --> 00:31:48,111
It's called a junkanoo.

389
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:51,675
'I'm not hearing
anything up here, buddy.'

390
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:55,474
How many have you tagged, exactly?
How many?

391
00:31:55,520 --> 00:31:59,718
Michael... stop busting my bunghie.

392
00:31:59,760 --> 00:32:03,230
Yeah, it's OK for you,
but not for me, huh?

393
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:05,555
Have no fear, Jake is here.

394
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:08,478
I just struck the mother lode.
I'm counting.

395
00:32:08,520 --> 00:32:12,399
'Watch yourself with
that fancy equipment, buddy.'

396
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:15,432
Such a live wire'll
make your hair stick up funny.

397
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:17,596
That's good, Michael. William?

398
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:19,870
Yeah, there's no hope for that boy.

399
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:23,310
Jake? Jake, that's a joke.

400
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:27,472
Holy shit!

401
00:32:31,960 --> 00:32:34,190
We got a big fish down here, man.

402
00:32:34,240 --> 00:32:36,515
Oh, yeah? How big?

403
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:42,188
- Jesus!
- Look out!

404
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:47,393
What's wrong?

405
00:32:51,040 --> 00:32:52,439
Ellen?

406
00:32:56,640 --> 00:32:58,392
Jesus Christ!

407
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:06,713
- Ellen, what's wrong?
- Nothing. Nothing. I'm fine.

408
00:33:06,760 --> 00:33:09,399
- No, you're not.
- I'm terrific.

409
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:18,834
Come on!

410
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:23,389
Give it up!

411
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:25,510
You can't keep doing this.

412
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:29,633
- I can't keep doing THIS.
- You promised me a drink.

413
00:33:29,680 --> 00:33:34,037
Sharks come and go, Ellen.
People have nothing to do with it.

414
00:33:34,080 --> 00:33:38,949
- A drink with an umbrella in it.
- Ellen, give it up.

415
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:42,036
Give it a kick in the arse.

416
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:44,036
Get on with your life.

417
00:33:51,640 --> 00:33:53,631
I know what you've been through.

418
00:33:53,680 --> 00:33:56,513
Don't worry.
The nightmares'll go away.

419
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:03,313
Give me my glasses, man.

420
00:34:03,360 --> 00:34:06,830
Boy, I ain't never seen
nothin' so big. Never!

421
00:34:06,880 --> 00:34:10,350
I was right next to Michael.
The thing went right past me!

422
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:13,198
Should've gone for you, Jake.
Why did it come up?

423
00:34:13,240 --> 00:34:16,516
- What's it doing in warm water?
- What's the difference?

424
00:34:16,600 --> 00:34:20,434
It's only a shark.
A big, big, beautiful shark.

425
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:23,278
And it's ours.
Don't say anything to anyone.

426
00:34:23,320 --> 00:34:28,394
Fishermen would try to kill it.
Michael, we got us a great white.

427
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:30,590
Now we gonna do some real research.

428
00:34:30,640 --> 00:34:34,428
Do me a favour, don't say
anything about this to my mom.

429
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:40,109
Hey, man, I didn't mean to,
you know, flap my lips, eh?

430
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:05,276
So...
So?

431
00:35:05,320 --> 00:35:09,279
I said to him,
"Where's the disinfectant?"

432
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:15,350
He said, "I've left it in town."

433
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:18,119
So I said,
"What are we gonna do?"

434
00:35:18,160 --> 00:35:21,436
So he says,
"I'll tell you what we'll do.

435
00:35:21,480 --> 00:35:25,632
"Come back at lunchtime, all the
flies will be in the kitchen."

436
00:35:28,040 --> 00:35:30,600
Come to bed.

437
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:34,756
He took her sightseeing.

438
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:37,313
Well, you work. I work.

439
00:35:37,360 --> 00:35:41,194
She needs someone to help her
take her mind off things.

440
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:58,036
I'll help you take YOUR mind
off things, sailor.

441
00:36:09,720 --> 00:36:11,551
It's soaking.

442
00:36:12,960 --> 00:36:15,599
Thank you.

443
00:36:18,840 --> 00:36:20,717
Good night.

444
00:36:25,040 --> 00:36:26,871
Good night.

445
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:49,034
Louisa.

446
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:51,753
It's OK, Jake.
I'll check on the table.

447
00:36:53,680 --> 00:36:57,434
- OK, everything rides.
-Ooh, it's Hoagie!

448
00:36:57,480 --> 00:36:59,630
Hey, come on, I wanna see this.

449
00:36:59,680 --> 00:37:01,750
Oh, that's Hoagie, all right.

450
00:37:05,160 --> 00:37:07,674
Everything on the line.

451
00:37:07,720 --> 00:37:10,757
- You're not betting it all?
- All or nothing at all.

452
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:13,678
- Here, do you want to throw for me?
- No!

453
00:37:13,720 --> 00:37:15,870
Now get ready. Are you ready?

454
00:37:28,840 --> 00:37:31,991
- I guess that's bad?
- Depends on your point of view.

455
00:37:32,040 --> 00:37:34,998
Ooh, look at that. Come here.

456
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:37,878
Ooh, look at you. You look great!

457
00:37:40,200 --> 00:37:41,633
It's on the house.

458
00:37:41,680 --> 00:37:44,274
I knew there was a reason
I could afford this.

459
00:37:44,320 --> 00:37:45,673
Thank you, Shirley!

460
00:37:45,720 --> 00:37:49,998
My father used to say, "Jake,
you got two loves in your life -

461
00:37:50,040 --> 00:37:52,634
"what you do and who you're with."

462
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:57,509
- Happy birthday, Louisa.
- Happy birthday!

463
00:37:57,560 --> 00:38:00,632
- And a Happy New Year.
- Happy New Year!

464
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:03,513
- Happy New Year.
- Happy New Year.

465
00:38:03,560 --> 00:38:06,028
Don't go weak in the knees
on me tonight, boy.

466
00:38:06,080 --> 00:38:08,719
You're gonna need
all the strength you got.

467
00:38:08,760 --> 00:38:10,830
I knew a one-armed piano player,

468
00:38:10,880 --> 00:38:13,474
took two minutes
to play the Minute Waltz.

469
00:38:15,840 --> 00:38:19,389
Watch how you talk.
Michael and I are about to be famous.

470
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:20,714
- Tell 'em.
- Jake!

471
00:38:20,760 --> 00:38:22,910
No job talk. You promised.

472
00:38:22,960 --> 00:38:25,110
You promised.

473
00:38:25,160 --> 00:38:27,310
Right.

474
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:29,749
Would you risk
a dance with me, madam?

475
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:33,236
- You'll be sorry.
- So will you. I have two right feet.

476
00:38:33,280 --> 00:38:35,510
That's good, I have two left.

477
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:37,073
Well, that's a set.

478
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:51,868
A little quiet tonight.

479
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:54,354
- New Year's blues?
- No, not at all.

480
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:57,472
Come on. It's my party.

481
00:38:57,520 --> 00:39:01,911
He's just Michael, he's startin' to
count them damn conch in his sleep.

482
00:39:03,360 --> 00:39:04,634
Excuse me.

483
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:17,670
- Mind if I cut in?
- Please.

484
00:39:17,720 --> 00:39:19,870
The world would be a better place

485
00:39:19,920 --> 00:39:22,434
if more sons danced
with their mothers.

486
00:39:28,280 --> 00:39:30,748
Michael, stop pouting.

487
00:39:30,800 --> 00:39:35,510
You look like you did when you were
six and didn't get what you wanted.

488
00:39:35,560 --> 00:39:38,472
