01:01:04,160 --> 01:01:06,913
Hey, hey, hey!
Hey, what you doin', man?

731
01:01:06,960 --> 01:01:10,555
No one goes in the water
till we know where that fish is.

732
01:01:10,600 --> 01:01:13,273
You fall off the horse,
you get right back on.

733
01:01:13,320 --> 01:01:16,437
Hell, what kind of bullcrap
you talkin'? Huh?

734
01:01:16,480 --> 01:01:20,632
- Anybody's in the water, it's me.
- Jake, I'm gonna go down.

735
01:01:20,680 --> 01:01:25,515
All right, so what about Carla's gig?
It's almost time, man.

736
01:01:29,960 --> 01:01:32,838
Michael, I can't just let you
go back down.

737
01:01:35,240 --> 01:01:36,958
I'm scared shitless.

738
01:01:37,000 --> 01:01:40,436
What the hell do I do
if I can't go back in that water?

739
01:01:43,240 --> 01:01:44,753
All right, be careful.

740
01:01:57,400 --> 01:02:00,949
Clarence, get up on that shack.
Give us some lookout.

741
01:02:01,000 --> 01:02:05,312
- I hope he knows what he's doing.
- He's doin' what he's got to do.

742
01:02:20,240 --> 01:02:23,073
Jake, are you gettin'
anything on the shark?

743
01:02:27,600 --> 01:02:29,989
No, everything's cool.

744
01:02:30,040 --> 01:02:33,396
I'm thinkin' about yesterday.
It's probably a mistake.

745
01:02:33,440 --> 01:02:37,149
- He was hungry. You look tasty.
- But how come only me?

746
01:02:37,200 --> 01:02:41,591
- Maybe he just like white meat.
- You're a funny guy, Jake.

747
01:02:45,200 --> 01:02:46,519
Jesus!

748
01:02:58,080 --> 01:03:02,312
It is about art
that I wish to speak today.

749
01:03:03,360 --> 01:03:07,876
The raw material of art
surrounds us all,

750
01:03:07,920 --> 01:03:12,072
catching in the net that each
and every one of us casts

751
01:03:12,120 --> 01:03:14,475
into the current of life.

752
01:03:15,840 --> 01:03:19,196
- But it takes the art...
- Where the hell are they?

753
01:03:19,240 --> 01:03:20,958
They'll be here.

754
01:03:21,000 --> 01:03:23,150
- Can I go on the banana boat?
- Shh!

755
01:03:23,200 --> 01:03:26,397
Margaret's going.
She's with her mother.

756
01:03:26,440 --> 01:03:28,749
- OK.
- Oh, boy! Oh, boy!

757
01:03:28,800 --> 01:03:31,519
- Thea, you be careful.
- I will, I will!

758
01:03:31,560 --> 01:03:34,632
- Thea!
- It's OK. Banana boats are fun.

759
01:03:35,680 --> 01:03:39,798
Oh, we should be so lucky.
I wish we were out with her playin'.

760
01:03:39,840 --> 01:03:42,070
Margaret, wait for me!

761
01:03:42,120 --> 01:03:46,511
"Get to the point, man,"
as my wife now says.

762
01:03:48,480 --> 01:03:54,112
OK. Well, in short, art is grease
for the wheel of life.

763
01:03:54,160 --> 01:04:00,269
Today we are privileged
to dedicate a work of art.

764
01:04:00,320 --> 01:04:01,992
Carla Brody,

765
01:04:02,040 --> 01:04:06,795
an artist of growing reputation,

766
01:04:06,840 --> 01:04:12,949
was commissioned to express
our way of life in permanent form...

767
01:04:13,000 --> 01:04:16,549
to show the world what we all know
right here on this beach:

768
01:04:16,600 --> 01:04:19,433
That it is better in the Bahamas.

769
01:04:19,520 --> 01:04:27,359
- Absolutely.
- Ladies and gentlemen, Carla Brody!

770
01:04:27,400 --> 01:04:31,154
Thank you, Commissioner Witherspoon,
Mrs Witherspoon.

771
01:04:38,440 --> 01:04:40,192
Thea!

772
01:04:46,720 --> 01:04:48,153
Oh, my God!

773
01:04:50,600 --> 01:04:51,828
Thea!

774
01:04:54,560 --> 01:04:57,632
Stop! Come back! Bring her back!

775
01:04:59,760 --> 01:05:01,034
Oh, my God!

776
01:05:15,280 --> 01:05:17,953
Stop! Thea! Thea!

777
01:05:18,000 --> 01:05:19,274
Thea!

778
01:05:19,320 --> 01:05:21,470
Somebody do something!

779
01:05:26,240 --> 01:05:27,468
Thea!

780
01:05:33,360 --> 01:05:34,679
Oh, no! My God!

781
01:05:45,200 --> 01:05:48,476
- Mommy! Mommy!
- Thea!

782
01:05:50,160 --> 01:05:53,789
Somebody get a doctor!
Get a doctor now!

783
01:05:53,840 --> 01:05:55,717
Quickly!

784
01:06:58,720 --> 01:07:01,917
- I'm sorry I missed you.
- Where have you been?

785
01:07:01,960 --> 01:07:03,951
What's the matter? What happened?

786
01:07:04,000 --> 01:07:06,036
Thea was attacked by a shark.

787
01:07:06,080 --> 01:07:07,991
Oh, my God.

788
01:07:09,040 --> 01:07:11,918
The doctor said she should be OK.
She's in shock.

789
01:07:11,960 --> 01:07:15,635
Sweetheart? Sweetheart?

790
01:07:15,680 --> 01:07:18,592
I'm so sorry.
I should've known. Jesus.

791
01:07:18,680 --> 01:07:20,511
Should've known what?

792
01:07:24,000 --> 01:07:26,560
- We tried to keep track of him.
- Of...

793
01:07:26,600 --> 01:07:28,477
The shark.

794
01:07:28,520 --> 01:07:31,080
- You knew?
- Yeah. Thought it went away.

795
01:07:31,120 --> 01:07:34,078
- Came after me.
- She could've been killed. You knew?

796
01:07:34,120 --> 01:07:37,157
And you didn't tell us?
You let your mother think...

797
01:07:37,200 --> 01:07:38,394
Where is she?

798
01:07:38,440 --> 01:07:41,079
- How could you do that?
- Where's my mother?

799
01:07:41,120 --> 01:07:43,588
- Where's my mother?
- Why didn't you tell us?

800
01:07:43,640 --> 01:07:47,030
- Where's Jake?
- WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL US?

801
01:07:49,960 --> 01:07:51,757
Michael!

802
01:07:55,120 --> 01:07:56,599
Jake!

803
01:07:56,640 --> 01:07:59,074
- Jake!
- What?

804
01:07:59,120 --> 01:08:01,475
Come on! I need you! Hurry up!

805
01:08:20,680 --> 01:08:23,513
Hoagie! Did you see our boat?

806
01:08:23,560 --> 01:08:26,393
- I just got here.
- My mother took it.

807
01:08:26,440 --> 01:08:30,228
- I hope she's a good sailor.
- A shark attacked Thea.

808
01:08:30,280 --> 01:08:32,271
She went after the damn thing.

809
01:08:32,360 --> 01:08:35,670
- She's gone after it?
- Yeah, we gotta stop her.

810
01:08:35,720 --> 01:08:39,474
In that?
Lt'll take all day in that bathtub.

811
01:08:39,520 --> 01:08:40,555
Got a better idea?

812
01:08:45,280 --> 01:08:46,838
I'll radio her position.

813
01:08:46,880 --> 01:08:50,031
The rescue boats will pick her up,
so don't worry.

814
01:08:50,080 --> 01:08:51,229
She'll be fine.

815
01:08:51,280 --> 01:08:54,238
She'll never find that bloody shark.
We couldn't.

816
01:08:54,280 --> 01:08:57,352
It'll find her.
What do you mean?

817
01:08:57,400 --> 01:09:00,073
She said it was coming.

818
01:09:00,120 --> 01:09:03,317
- What do you mean?
- What do you know?

819
01:09:03,360 --> 01:09:06,636
She thinks the shark
that killed Martin and Sean

820
01:09:06,680 --> 01:09:08,272
is following the family.

821
01:09:08,320 --> 01:09:11,551
Hey, he's not talkin'
about our shark, eh?

822
01:09:11,600 --> 01:09:14,478
What do you do when
you're not flying people?

823
01:09:14,560 --> 01:09:17,393
I deliver laundry.

824
01:09:17,440 --> 01:09:21,991
Hold on. What's that?
Let's have a look.

825
01:09:28,160 --> 01:09:29,559
Oh.

826
01:09:31,320 --> 01:09:33,709
It's a big ocean out there.

827
01:10:10,080 --> 01:10:12,514
Can't this thing go any faster?

828
01:10:12,560 --> 01:10:15,552
Any faster, this thing'll be
a flying Cuisinart

829
01:10:15,600 --> 01:10:17,591
and we'll be diced into oblivion.

830
01:10:44,600 --> 01:10:46,909
Come and get me,
you son of a bitch.

831
01:10:52,840 --> 01:10:55,400
There she is.
That's her right there.

832
01:10:57,760 --> 01:10:59,352
Is that what I think it is?

833
01:11:01,440 --> 01:11:03,635
- Mom...
- Hold on!

834
01:11:13,920 --> 01:11:15,592
Oh!

835
01:11:29,920 --> 01:11:33,515
'Thomas, you there?
This is Zero-Papa-Alpha here.'

836
01:11:33,560 --> 01:11:35,710
'Hoagie, where are you? '

837
01:11:35,760 --> 01:11:40,072
12 miles southeast of Emerald Key.
Look for Neptune's Folly.'

838
01:11:42,840 --> 01:11:46,435
I need two boats fast and somebody
who can kill a shark - a big one.

839
01:11:46,480 --> 01:11:49,552
'What're you doing? '
Practising landing.

840
01:11:49,600 --> 01:11:51,989
Hang on to your socks, lads.

841
01:11:52,040 --> 01:11:54,600
Wait! You sure you know
how to do this?

842
01:11:54,640 --> 01:11:58,189
Of course not!
What kind of pilot do you think I am?

843
01:12:11,760 --> 01:12:13,637
- Christ!
- Hell, not half bad.

844
01:12:13,680 --> 01:12:15,591
Get out, I'll keep it busy.

845
01:12:15,640 --> 01:12:19,633
No, it'll come for the plane's
electromagnetic impulse.

846
01:12:19,680 --> 01:12:22,240
Get the bloody hell out!

847
01:12:22,280 --> 01:12:23,474
Michael!

848
01:12:33,440 --> 01:12:38,798
Damn passengers! You're all the same.
Complain, complain...

849
01:12:38,840 --> 01:12:40,353
Oh, shit!

850
01:12:42,720 --> 01:12:43,755
Hoagie!

851
01:12:46,600 --> 01:12:49,433
Hoagie! Hoagie!

852
01:13:09,440 --> 01:13:12,352
Why'd you come out here?

853
01:13:15,480 --> 01:13:17,072
Why'd you come out here?

854
01:13:17,120 --> 01:13:19,270
- Why did you bring him?
- Mom, Mom!

855
01:13:19,320 --> 01:13:22,118
- Why'd you take the boat?
- It kept coming!

856
01:13:22,160 --> 01:13:25,516
- Didn't you realise?
- There was nothing else to do.

857
01:13:25,600 --> 01:13:28,797
- You shouldn't have done it.
- I tried to tell you.

858
01:13:28,840 --> 01:13:31,229
I tried.

859
01:13:35,760 --> 01:13:38,638
Hey!
Give me a hand, for Christ's sake!

860
01:13:38,680 --> 01:13:41,638
- Hoagie!
- How the hell did you do that, man?

861
01:13:41,680 --> 01:13:44,478
- It wasn't easy, believe me.
- Get him up.

862
01:13:47,680 --> 01:13:49,716
You all right, man?

863
01:13:49,760 --> 01:13:52,991
- Oh! Bloody hell.
- Get it started!

864
01:13:53,040 --> 01:13:55,998
- The breath on that thing!
- You are alive!

865
01:13:56,040 --> 01:13:58,474
Let's get out of here,
Ellen Brody. Oh!

866
01:13:58,520 --> 01:14:00,795
Good, this thing's still working.

867
01:14:01,880 --> 01:14:04,155
That's your engine, pal.
I'll have a look.

868
01:14:07,760 --> 01:14:09,955
Oh, shit, he's close, man.

869
01:14:10,000 --> 01:14:13,117
- What is that sound?
- The shark's heartbeat.

870
01:14:13,160 --> 01:14:16,869
Hoagie, try to finish.
Michael, gimme a hand, I got an idea.

871
01:14:16,920 --> 01:14:20,833
We're taking water down here.
Ellen, start pumping here.

872
01:14:21,880 --> 01:14:24,792
Ellen! Get the bilge pump!

873
01:14:24,840 --> 01:14:29,231
Take the radio transmitter out
and hook it to the strobe.

874
01:14:29,280 --> 01:14:32,716
- We gotta get the engine started!
- Just do it!

875
01:14:32,760 --> 01:14:35,718
We're gonna feed that big boy
a meal he won't forget.

876
01:14:35,760 --> 01:14:40,072
You better have something good going.
We've got a rotten hose.

877
01:14:40,120 --> 01:14:43,396
There's a spare one.
What you wanna do with this?

878
01:14:43,440 --> 01:14:48,468
I'm riggin' the receiver. We get it
inside that bastard and set it off.

879
01:14:48,520 --> 01:14:52,479
I got it. We rig an antenna on this,
we can shock the hell out of him.

880
01:14:52,520 --> 01:14:53,999
Right! You're learning.

881
01:14:57,280 --> 01:14:58,759
He's getting closer!

882
01:14:58,800 --> 01:15:03,430
They spend their lives looking for
food, they don't care what it is.

883
01:15:03,480 --> 01:15:06,313
Maybe he's got indigestion.
He's eaten my plane!

884
01:15:08,280 --> 01:15:10,396
It's not food he's after.

885
01:15:10,440 --> 01:15:13,273
Michael, turn on your switch.
I need a test.

886
01:15:13,320 --> 01:15:16,198
- Anybody tell you you're nuts?
- All the time.

887
01:15:16,240 --> 01:15:19,198
If it responds
to external electrical impulse,

888
01:15:19,240 --> 01:15:22,949
it might respond to one inside -
confuse him, drive him crazy.

889
01:15:23,000 --> 01:15:25,639
OK, a test... Good.

890
01:15:29,480 --> 01:15:33,189
You'd better get up here!
The heartbeat's stopped!

891
01:15:38,640 --> 01:15:40,232
Shit.

892
01:15:40,280 --> 01:15:43,795
Either he's gone
or your gear's crapped out again.

893
01:15:44,840 --> 01:15:49,072
That's bull. My equipment
don't crap out. He'll be back.

894
01:15:49,120 --> 01:15:51,793
Get me the boat hook.

895
01:15:51,840 --> 01:15:56,436
Maybe he had a heart attack.
Humans are full of cholesterol.

896
01:15:56,480 --> 01:15:58,550
- Give me that.
- Shit! Where is he?

897
01:16:00,600 --> 01:16:03,512
Give me that line, Michael.
Right there.

898
01:16:04,560 --> 01:16:05,993
There he is!

899
01:16:07,840 --> 01:16:10,308
Ellen, try the engine.

900
01:16:11,640 --> 01:16:13,949
Ellen! Try to start the engine!

901
01:16:18,600 --> 01:16:21,592
Son of a bitch.
Let's get out of here.

902
01:16:21,640 --> 01:16:25,679
No, it's too late, Hoagie.
Give me a hard port.

903
01:16:25,720 --> 01:16:27,438
Right!

904
01:16:27,480 --> 01:16:32,156
Here, give me that.
No! No time for that!

905
01:16:32,200 --> 01:16:35,158
Jake! You can't go out there
without a line!

906
01:16:37,800 --> 01:16:40,519
Keep it steady.
It's gonna come back!

907
01:16:57,200 --> 01:17:00,317
Damn thing's disappeared. He's gone!

908
01:17:35,600 --> 01:17:41,789
Jake!

909
01:18:08,800 --> 01:18:11,951
We're taking too much water.
It'll stop the engine.

910
01:18:12,000 --> 01:18:15,037
Ellen, take the wheel.
We've got to outrun it. Ellen!

911
01:18:31,440 --> 01:18:35,115
- That thing gonna work?
- It'll work.

912
01:18:35,160 --> 01:18:38,436
If Jake says so, it will.
This charge will drive it crazy.

913
01:19:39,800 --> 01:19:42,872
Sweet Jesus,
we're headed straight for it!

914
01:19:42,920 --> 01:19:45,309
Ellen, come about!

915
01:19:51,120 --> 01:19:54,715
We're gonna hit it!
Hold on!

916
01:19:54,760 --> 01:19:56,239
Hold on!

917
01:19:57,400 --> 01:19:59,595
Smile, you son of a bitch!

918
01:20:25,040 --> 01:20:26,189
- Michael!
- Come over here.

919
01:20:30,240 --> 01:20:31,639
Michael!

920
01:20:31,680 --> 01:20:34,319
It's all right! I'm OK!

921
01:20:34,360 --> 01:20:37,477
Anybody there? Over here!

922
01:20:40,680 --> 01:20:41,908
Jake!

923
01:20:44,440 --> 01:20:47,079
Michael, you got a minute?

924
01:20:47,120 --> 01:20:49,554
It's Jake!

925
01:20:52,320 --> 01:20:54,276
Son of a bitch!

926
01:21:04,760 --> 01:21:06,591
Jesus, Jake.

927
01:21:10,040 --> 01:21:13,715
What took you so damn long, man?

928
01:21:13,760 --> 01:21:16,149
What the hell are you doing alive?

929
01:21:16,200 --> 01:21:19,909
I told you Uncle Jake's
equipment don't crap out, eh?

930
01:21:22,640 --> 01:21:26,519
You're not going to do something
stupid like die on me, are you?

931
01:21:26,560 --> 01:21:30,075
No, man. I'm way too mean for that.

932
01:21:36,960 --> 01:21:40,032
So from now on,
we're going to study snails, eh?

933
01:21:40,080 --> 01:21:41,672
Yeah.

934
01:21:46,200 --> 01:21:48,589
Come to Amity this summer.

935
01:21:48,640 --> 01:21:51,712
We'll be there.
You make sure they come.

936
01:21:51,760 --> 01:21:54,354
I will.
I'll miss you, Grandma.

937
01:21:56,040 --> 01:21:58,952
Get in, Ellen Brody.
You'll miss your plane.

938
01:21:59,000 --> 01:22:01,468
- Goodbye, Grandma!
- OK.

939
01:22:01,560 --> 01:22:03,835
- Be careful.
- OK. See ya.

940
01:22:04,920 --> 01:22:07,275
- Take good care of Jake.
- I will.

941
01:22:08,720 --> 01:22:11,280
You gonna be OK?

942
01:22:11,320 --> 01:22:14,312
- Yeah.
- OK.

943
01:22:15,120 --> 01:22:18,749
When I come back,
remind me to tell you about the time

944
01:22:18,800 --> 01:22:21,030
I took a hundred nuns to Nairobi.

945
01:22:26,520 --> 01:22:30,149
There they were,
100 nuns, playing guitars

946
01:22:30,200 --> 01:22:34,113
and singing, "The hills are alive
with the sound of music."

947
01:22:34,160 --> 01:22:37,789
Then suddenly,
one comes up to me and she says,

948
01:22:37,840 --> 01:22:40,798
"There's smoke coming
from the engine."

949
01:22:40,840 --> 01:22:43,593
But I never
took them seriously,

950
01:22:43,640 --> 01:22:46,712
until they all started singing
"Nearer My God to Thee."

951
01:22:47,712 --> 01:22:57,712
